{
  "texts": [
    "These values are found to be:S z c (t → ∞) = -0.25, S cf (t → ∞) = -0.25, and E c kin (t → ∞)/t0 = 0.0.and the oscillation amplitude becomes larger, while the oscillation frequency remains practically unchanged.In addition, the z-component of the conduction electron S z c and the total local spin correlations S cf approach a steady state without any apparent J-dependence.",
    "On the one hand, S z c [see Fig. 2(a)] approaches S z c → -0.5, i.e., the electronic spin flips entirely from 1/2 to -1/2, becoming parallel to the initial spin orientation of the localized spins.",
    "On the other hand, S cf → 0.25 [see Fig. 2(b)].",
    "Contrary to the expectation values of these two operators, the long-time behavior of the electronic kinetic energy, shown in Fig. 2(c), retains a clear dependence on the Kondo coupling J.",
    "To be specific, the total energy transfer to the local spin chain scales linearly as ∆E c kin = -J/2."
  ]
}